<TITLE> Chittagong Press Club, court on bomb alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)--Security has been beefed up around Chittagong Press Club and court premises after unnamed persons issued bomb threats on Thursday. Messages containing the threat were sent to the press club president Abu Sufian and general secretary Rashed Rouf. Rouf told bdnews24.com he had received the message on his mobile phone at around 12:30am that said time bombs would be set off at the press club and court premises any time between 10am and 2pm. RAB, police forces and intelligence agencies were informed of the threat. Chittagong Metropolitan Police deputy commissioner Banaj Kumar Majumder said they had visited the spot. "In addition to deployment of additional police forces, we have searched the premises as well as suspected people there," he added. 
